      <item>
        <title>What the web</title>
        <link>/en/notebook/html-css/2020/10/15/What-the-web.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">/en/notebook/html-css/2020/10/15/What-the-web.html</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;What is the web actually? How do our browsers show us a webpage?&lt;br /&gt;
As you already known, web browsers  are based on WebKit.
The browser is like the middle man (Browser Engine). 
When we type www.google.com and hit enter (User Interface), 
the browser will go to Google’s server and ask for HTML-CSS files. 
The server will hand those files to that middle man. 
Then the middle man will give it to a cook (Rendering Engine). 
Finally, the cook will display the dish back to middle man, then to us.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are couple things to explore:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;WebKit&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Browser Engine&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Server&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;User Interface&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Rendering Engines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(to be cont. when I get wiser…)&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
        <pubDate>Thu, 15 Oct 2020 00:00:00 -0700</pubDate>
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Basic Git commands</title>
        <link>/en/notebook/git/2020/09/25/Basic-Git-Commands.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">/en/notebook/git/2020/09/25/Basic-Git-Commands.html</guid>
        <description>&lt;h4 id=&quot;first-you-thinking-of-create-a-project-for-your-class-so-you-need-to-create-a-repo&quot;&gt;First, you thinking of create a project for your class so you need to create a repo:&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Create a new repo:
    &lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-git&quot;&gt;git init
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Rename local branch:&lt;br /&gt;
   https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6591213/how-do-i-rename-a-local-git-branch
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git branch -m &amp;lt;oldname&amp;gt; &amp;lt;newname&amp;gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;To check your local branch you can use:
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git branch
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;To check your remote branch
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git branch -r
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;the-project-is-expand-and-you-invite-someone-to-work-with-you&quot;&gt;The project is expand and you invite someone to work with you&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;If you invite someone to work with you, they will use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git clone &amp;lt;https://link_to_your_repo&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;They can create a new branch using&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git branch &amp;lt;lulu&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Then switch to &lt;strong&gt;lulu&lt;/strong&gt; using&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git check out lulu&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;When &lt;strong&gt;lulu&lt;/strong&gt; trying to pull using &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git pull&lt;/code&gt;,  she’ll have a problem like this&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ git pull
There is no tracking information for the current branch.
Please specify which branch you want to merge with.
See git-pull(1) for details.
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So she have to pull from origin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Another coworker create a new branch as lala &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git branch lala&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;lala  use &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git pull&lt;/code&gt; and have the same error, lala has to use &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git branch&lt;/code&gt; and find the master branch.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;lala has to use &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git branch&lt;/code&gt; and find the default.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Since working, lala has made many contributions, so a manager want to make lala branch as a default branch or master branch.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Another words, manager want to merge &lt;strong&gt;lala branch&lt;/strong&gt; into &lt;strong&gt;master branch&lt;/strong&gt;. To do it lala need to &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git add &amp;lt;lala_works&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git commit -m &quot;what does lala do&quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Then manager will &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git checkout master&lt;/code&gt; and then &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git merge lulu&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;another-scenario&quot;&gt;Another scenario:&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We assign lala  to work on PHP side only&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;tips&quot;&gt;tips&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you are tired of commit, add, push, you can try oneliner like this :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git commit -a -m &quot;commit&quot; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; git push
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
        <pubDate>Fri, 25 Sep 2020 00:00:00 -0700</pubDate>
      </item>
    
